data.name: Голубці (Cabbage Rolls)
data.quickTastyDescription: Tender cabbage rolls stuffed with a savory mixture of rice and meat, simmered in a rich tomato sauce.
detailedCookingInstructions: Prepare the cabbage by removing the core and blanching the leaves in boiling water for about 2 minutes until pliable.
In a bowl, mix together the ground meat, cooked rice, chopped onion, minced garlic, salt, pepper, and dried herbs.
Take a cabbage leaf, place a spoonful of the meat mixture at the base, fold in the sides, and roll up tightly. Repeat with remaining leaves.
In a large pot, spread some tomato sauce at the bottom, arrange the cabbage rolls seam side down, and cover with the rest of the tomato sauce.
Bring to a simmer over medium heat, cover, and cook for about 60 minutes until the meat is cooked through and the cabbage is tender.
data.modifiersForBase: Stuffed with meat and rice, simmered in tomato sauce
